[[https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0042][— BIP42 by sipa]]

* Major bugs (2/2)

- Jan 2009: `OP_CHECKMULTISIG` eats extra value from stack
: Multisig off by one, need to have extra stack item
- Aug 2010: ~184 billion BTC accidentally created: [[https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Value_overflow_incident][CVE-2010-5139]]
- Mar 2013: 24 block chainsplit and hardfork: [[https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0050.mediawiki][BIP50]], [[https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2013-3220][CVE-2013-3220]]
: hardfork when blocks requiring more fds than < 0.8 could handle crashed those nodes
- Apr 2014: made monetary supply finite in [[https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0042.mediawiki][BIP42]]
- Sep 2018: potential coin inflation in [[https://bitcoincore.org/en/2018/09/20/notice/][CVE-2018-17144]]
: certain type of block could double spend outputs in the same block, creating coins out of thin air

